body:
Endgame Premiere.

Word Count: 2.2k

Category: Fluff

Warning: None

Summary: Proud boyfriend Harry attends girlfriend’s Endgame movie premiere.

—

All the moments lead up to this.

Moments of Harry hardly seeing you. Moments of when you would cry in frustration because you had a bad shooting day. Moments of when Harry would bring you lunch on set, a small note with a “Have a good day! Kick arses! I love you. x” attached to it.

It had been tiring. And for Harry, it had been worrying too.

When you came home with a busted lip and a deep red scratch near your eye? He lost it. Eyes wide, hands sweating and a still body.

“I know it looks like I had been at a fight, I wasn’t. I’m okay, I promise.” You had said slowly, wanting to get it through his head that no, you didn’t need to go to the hospital and no, he shouldn’t start setting 15 alarms on your phone to remind you to take your vitamins.

You and Harry met through Lou. Your makeup artist had gotten sick when you needed her and it seemed like watching a YouTube tutorial gave you next to no knowledge on how to accurately apply eyeliner. Your manager contacted another makeup artist who was fortunately free at the time of your event; the one and only Lou Teasdale.

From there, she was your go-to. Ditching the videos that taught you nothing but how much of a beginner you were and how there were much more than just lipstick to apply on your lips, Lou became a friend and a tutor.

She had taught you how to apply the “no makeup-makeup” look and after trying it on yourself and liking it, you wanted to try it on someone else.

It just so happened that Harry was visiting her.

Harry knew you were both friends at the time, having had ticked Lou off and almost begged her to let you both meet, he was gobsmacked when he saw you sitting on her sofa with w makeup brush in your hand and a bright smile on your face,

“Hey, I’m Y/N!”

Of course he knew who you were. Everyone did. How can no one know the academy award winner who appeared in most successful and hit movies of the last few years?

It went upwards from there and it led to the relationship of three years and a cat, Evie.

“Are you ready?” Harry asks from outside the door, wide grin on his face as it beams with excitement, he’s eager.

“Just a minute!” You reply, applying the last coat of mascara on your face and taking one last look at yourself.

You were in a black tuxedo, no shirt underneath as the blazer was buttoned with a long V-neck, hair slicked back, red lipstick on your lips.

You take a deep breath before opening the door, flinching when you realise just how close Harry was to the door.

His eyes widen, eyebrows going up as he looks at you up and down before releasing a wolf whistle that had you rolling your eyes as you blush, trying to suppress your giggle.

“You really are a superwoman.”

You laugh, shaking your head, “That has to be the worst line you have ever used on me.”

“Come on, I’ve been practicing it all day.” He jokes, smiling childishly as he looks at you before wrapping his arms around your waist, “You look so fucking good right now. You’re,” He pauses, squinting his eyes, “Endgame.”

“Oh my God, you’re awful!”

Arriving at the premiere, the fans and cameras seemed to be anticipating your arrival because as soon as you and Harry step out of the car, it goes wild.

Harry’s hand is around your waist as you both walk, both of you giggling to each other about the reaction.

“Was waiting for you!” Tom Holland approaches you with a grin, perky as he hugs you before moving to Harry, “Been so long since I’ve seen you, mate! How are you?”

You giggle at Tom’s eager character, watching as him and your boyfriend interact before the three of you stand and pose for the camera, you in the middle.

“Your girlfriend slapped the shit out of me in the movie. For being from the nice people, she d-“

“You’re going to spoil something.” You warn cautiously.

“I mean, I get that she has a rough past but my character seems to tick her off, although at the end, she hu-“

“Tom.”

“-ugs me and I think it shows that we’re going to have a siblings bond. You know she’s appearing my next SpiderMan movie, right?”

“For fuck’s sake, Tom!”

“What?!” Harry’s eyes widen and as does his smile, “Baby, you didn’t tell me.”

“That’s because,” You smile sarcastically as you look at Tom, “It was supposed to be a surprise.”

Tom’s eyes go wide, hand clasping to his mouth, “I shouldn’t have said that.”

“Kid causing you trouble?” Everyone would know that voice anywhere. Robert appears in front of you, “Nice to see you, Harry. Still Team Tony, aren’t you?”

Harry chuckles, hugging the man, “Always.”

“Wrong movie reference, rockstar.” Chris Hemsworth jokes, “Let me hug him, Rob.”

“Can you make your crush on my boyfriend any clearer?” You joke, putting your arm around Tom’s shoulders as he stands shorter than you.

“If I try, I’m going to end up marrying him.”

“There’s enough of me to share.” Harry adds, making everyone laugh as you begin to stand next to each other, posing for the eager cameras.

One photo is with Harry in the middle, you pretending to pull his left arm while Chris pulls the right one, Harry smirking for the cameras. One is of you, Harry and Tom, Tom in the middle as he wraps his arms around both of your shoulders, looking as a kid whose parents took him to the zoo.

Robert takes one of the both of you kissing each of his cheeks, having claimed that you and Harry were his love children numerous times.

“Hey, you hogged them up without telling us!” Mark attempts to seem cross but makes you laugh nevertheless, seeing him walking towards you with Scarlett and Paul, who pulls you into a group hug.

“Harry, you’re not ready to see her in the movie.” Paul raises his eyebrows, pursing his lips as he points at Harry.

Harry grins, wrapping his arm around your waist as you all smile to the cameras, “I’m never ready when it comes to her.” He leans forward, pecking your cheek quickly, knowing well what it’d do for the paps and fans.

“Alright, couple photos. Let’s leave them. Come on, party’s over.” Robert waves your cast mates off jokingly, looking back at you and giving you a wink which have you and Harry laughing.

“Party just started, old man.” You grin widely as Chris Evans walks towards you.

“Save your breath, he’s still team Tony.” Robert puts his hand up, stopping Chris from reaching Harry.

“Nonsense, Harry’s team Cap. He knows better.” Chris feigns shock.

“Which is why he’s team Tony.”

“Sometimes I can’t believe that you both aren’t 6.” You shake your head jokingly.

You and Harry walk towards the reporters, hands intertwined securely with each other as you approach a man.

“Y/N, Harry! You look amazing tonight!”

“Thank you, you look great yourself.” You smile, hearing Harry thanking the man as well.

“Who are you wearing, Y/N?”

“I’m wearing Gucci tonight. Feeling Gucci.” You look down at yourself before smiling up.

“Would you say that’s Harry’s impact?”

“It definitely is,” Harry chuckles, “It definitely is.”

“Harry, are you excited to see the movie? Any predictions?”

“I’m very excited. Very proud of this one right here. And no,” He shakes his head slightly, “No predictions. Every time I predict something, it never happens and my mind gets blown.”

“He saved his breath this time.” You pat Harry’s chest.

“That’s a smart decision,” The reporter jokes, “Well have a good night!”

You both pose for more pictures, you pose for solo ones and cast ones and before you know it, it’s time to see the movie.

“Very tempted to throw popcorn at people right now.” You say as you sit, Harry sitting beside you with your popcorn bucket in his hand.

He hushes you with a giggle, putting on his 3D glasses, “My girl’s in that movie and I’d rather watch her than get kicked out.”

You blush, wearing your glasses as if it’d hide the flustered look on your face.

“Can’t believe you fuck villains up and get shy when I say stuff like that.”

“Hush, movie’s starting.”

“As you say so, gorgeous.”

—

It’s like Harry entered a world of his own. By the 10th minute, he stopped eating popcorn and you know it isn’t because he was full, Lord knows he can finish 3 buckets on his own, but he was way too engrossed in the movie to miss a single letter over the noisy grains.

Seeing your hard work come to life is one the best feelings in the world, but seeing how Harry was into the movie, that’s a whole other thing.

He gasped, muttered incoherent words under his breath, gave quiet orders to the characters as if they heard him and he cried. You watch as he grins when you appear in front of Thanos, absentmindedly giving one clap of excitement that leaves you amused as you watch him lovingly.

However, his grin falters when your character is thrown in the air by Thanos, going to the edge of his seat.

You mentally prepare yourself for the next scene, now knowing fully well that your boyfriend won’t take it well.

In the scene, Thanos walks towards you, grips your throat as he raises you in the air, words of spite thrown at you.

“That fucker, no.” Harry mumbles under his breath, “I swear to God if she dies,”

He doesn’t get to finish his sentence when Captain America hits Thanos, making you drop as your character begins to catch breath.

This seems to be satisfying Harry because he releases a sigh of relief, sinking back in his chair before turning to look at you, “Thank God you’re okay.”

You’re still amused and flattered by his reaction, not processing when he leans to quickly peck your lips before going back to watching the movie.

By the end of the movie, Harry was emotional. As the movie ends, your boyfriend is the first person to stand and clap, everyone copying a second later as they applaud the cast and crew. Your eyes tear up, throwing yourself on Harry as you cry tears of joy.

His arms are wrapped tightly around you, head buried into your neck as he peppers your skin with soft kisses.

“That was so fucking good, that was so good,” He cups your face, “I’m mad proud of you. I have no words.”

“Yeah?”

“Yeah,” He nods rapidly, face beaming with pride as he leans down to press his lips against yours, “That was incredible. You were incredible, I can’t believe I get to call you my girlfriend.”

You smile through the tears, holding tightly to his hands on your cheeks as you press yourself closer to him, “How are you feeling?”

“How am I feeling?” He laughs, “I’m fucking wrecked, baby. I’m,” He stops to laugh slightly as he sniffles, “This ended me.”

“You’re not going to stop the puns, are you?”

“Not anytime soon, no.”

With one last kiss, you leave Harry as you walk with the cast towards the stage, accepting Chris Evans’s hand as he helps you up the stairs before you all stand side to side, you between Chris Pratt and Sebastian.

“Your man’s crying tears of pride right now.” Chris leans to the side towards you, pointing at Harry as he stands clapping with everyone else, eyes set solely on you.

You giggle as you gave him a shrug, “Won the lottery with that one.”

“You sure as hell did.” Seb agrees.

“Do you all seriously have a crush on him?”

“Have you seen him?! You can’t blame us.”

You smirk, pointing at Seb with a tilt of your head, “Good point.”

Harry’s the last one to sit, a wide grin on his face as Robert begins to talk, making eye contact with you and giving you eager thumbs up and blowing you a kiss, mouthing a cheeky “I love you”.

You’re a giggling mess, discreetly flipping Seb off as he cooes, waving at Harry with the other as you mouth back, “I love you”.

Harry is full of pride, he’s sure that if it was possible, he literally would be smiling from ear to ear. And when it was your turn to talk? He couldn’t not stand.

“God, this has been a journey,” You chuckle as you talk into the microphone, “There’s nothing in life that will come close to how this lifetime experience felt. This was never about going to set, shooting and going home. It was about making a family out every single one of this cast. This has felt like home and no matter what happens, this will always be home. So many people I’d like to thank but that’s going to take all night so let me just say that, I love you all so much,” You turn to look at your castmates who watch you with love and smiles, “Thank you so much for the opportunity and thank you,” You smile at the audience as you reach your arm out, “For being amazing and,” Your eyes fall on Harry as he stands with a hand on his heart, looking at you, “For supporting us.”

//

proud!boyfriend!harry is what we all need

“Come on, I’ve been practicing it all day.” He jokes, smiling childishly as he looks at you before wrapping his arms around your waist, “You look so fucking good right now. You’re,” He pauses, squinting his eyes, “Endgame.”

“Oh my God, you’re awful!”

Arriving at the premiere, the fans and cameras seemed to be anticipating your arrival because as soon as you and Harry step out of the car, it goes wild.

Harry’s hand is around your waist as you both walk, both of you giggling to each other about the reaction.

“Was waiting for you!” Tom Holland approaches you with a grin, perky as he hugs you before moving to Harry, “Been so long since I’ve seen you, mate! How are you?”

You giggle at Tom’s eager character, watching as him and your boyfriend interact before the three of you stand and pose for the camera, you in the middle.

“Your girlfriend slapped the shit out of me in the movie. For being from the nice people, she d-“

“You’re going to spoil something.” You warn cautiously.

“I mean, I get that she has a rough past but my character seems to tick her off, although at the end, she hu-“

“Tom.”

“-ugs me and I think it shows that we’re going to have a siblings bond. You know she’s appearing my next SpiderMan movie, right?”

“For fuck’s sake, Tom!”

“What?!” Harry’s eyes widen and as does his smile, “Baby, you didn’t tell me.”

“That’s because,” You smile sarcastically as you look at Tom, “It was supposed to be a surprise.”

Tom’s eyes go wide, hand clasping to his mouth, “I shouldn’t have said that.”

“Kid causing you trouble?” Everyone would know that voice anywhere. Robert appears in front of you, “Nice to see you, Harry. Still Team Tony, aren’t you?”

Harry chuckles, hugging the man, “Always.”

“Wrong movie reference, rockstar.” Chris Hemsworth jokes, “Let me hug him, Rob.”

“Can you make your crush on my boyfriend any clearer?” You joke, putting your arm around Tom’s shoulders as he stands shorter than you.

“If I try, I’m going to end up marrying him.”

“There’s enough of me to share.” Harry adds, making everyone laugh as you begin to stand next to each other, posing for the eager cameras.

One photo is with Harry in the middle, you pretending to pull his left arm while Chris pulls the right one, Harry smirking for the cameras. One is of you, Harry and Tom, Tom in the middle as he wraps his arms around both of your shoulders, looking as a kid whose parents took him to the zoo.

Robert takes one of the both of you kissing each of his cheeks, having claimed that you and Harry were his love children numerous times.

“Hey, you hogged them up without telling us!” Mark attempts to seem cross but makes you laugh nevertheless, seeing him walking towards you with Scarlett and Paul, who pulls you into a group hug.

“Harry, you’re not ready to see her in the movie.” Paul raises his eyebrows, pursing his lips as he points at Harry.

Harry grins, wrapping his arm around your waist as you all smile to the cameras, “I’m never ready when it comes to her.” He leans forward, pecking your cheek quickly, knowing well what it’d do for the paps and fans.

“Alright, couple photos. Let’s leave them. Come on, party’s over.” Robert waves your cast mates off jokingly, looking back at you and giving you a wink which have you and Harry laughing.

“Party just started, old man.” You grin widely as Chris Evans walks towards you.

“Save your breath, he’s still team Tony.” Robert puts his hand up, stopping Chris from reaching Harry.

“Nonsense, Harry’s team Cap. He knows better.” Chris feigns shock.

“Which is why he’s team Tony.”

“Sometimes I can’t believe that you both aren’t 6.” You shake your head jokingly.

You and Harry walk towards the reporters, hands intertwined securely with each other as you approach a man.

“Y/N, Harry! You look amazing tonight!”

“Thank you, you look great yourself.” You smile, hearing Harry thanking the man as well.

“Who are you wearing, Y/N?”

“I’m wearing Gucci tonight. Feeling Gucci.” You look down at yourself before smiling up.

“Would you say that’s Harry’s impact?”

“It definitely is,” Harry chuckles, “It definitely is.”

“Harry, are you excited to see the movie? Any predictions?”

“I’m very excited. Very proud of this one right here. And no,” He shakes his head slightly, “No predictions. Every time I predict something, it never happens and my mind gets blown.”

“He saved his breath this time.” You pat Harry’s chest.

“That’s a smart decision,” The reporter jokes, “Well have a good night!”

You both pose for more pictures, you pose for solo ones and cast ones and before you know it, it’s time to see the movie.

“Very tempted to throw popcorn at people right now.” You say as you sit, Harry sitting beside you with your popcorn bucket in his hand.

He hushes you with a giggle, putting on his 3D glasses, “My girl’s in that movie and I’d rather watch her than get kicked out.”

You blush, wearing your glasses as if it’d hide the flustered look on your face.

“Can’t believe you fuck villains up and get shy when I say stuff like that.”

“Hush, movie’s starting.”

“As you say so, gorgeous.”

—

It’s like Harry entered a world of his own. By the 10th minute, he stopped eating popcorn and you know it isn’t because he was full, Lord knows he can finish 3 buckets on his own, but he was way too engrossed in the movie to miss a single letter over the noisy grains.

Seeing your hard work come to life is one the best feelings in the world, but seeing how Harry was into the movie, that’s a whole other thing.

He gasped, muttered incoherent words under his breath, gave quiet orders to the characters as if they heard him and he cried. You watch as he grins when you appear in front of Thanos, absentmindedly giving one clap of excitement that leaves you amused as you watch him lovingly.

However, his grin falters when your character is thrown in the air by Thanos, going to the edge of his seat.

You mentally prepare yourself for the next scene, now knowing fully well that your boyfriend won’t take it well.

In the scene, Thanos walks towards you, grips your throat as he raises you in the air, words of spite thrown at you.

“That fucker, no.” Harry mumbles under his breath, “I swear to God if she dies,”

He doesn’t get to finish his sentence when Captain America hits Thanos, making you drop as your character begins to catch breath.

This seems to be satisfying Harry because he releases a sigh of relief, sinking back in his chair before turning to look at you, “Thank God you’re okay.”

You’re still amused and flattered by his reaction, not processing when he leans to quickly peck your lips before going back to watching the movie.

By the end of the movie, Harry was emotional. As the movie ends, your boyfriend is the first person to stand and clap, everyone copying a second later as they applaud the cast and crew. Your eyes tear up, throwing yourself on Harry as you cry tears of joy.

His arms are wrapped tightly around you, head buried into your neck as he peppers your skin with soft kisses.

“That was so fucking good, that was so good,” He cups your face, “I’m mad proud of you. I have no words.”

“Yeah?”

“Yeah,” He nods rapidly, face beaming with pride as he leans down to press his lips against yours, “That was incredible. You were incredible, I can’t believe I get to call you my girlfriend.”

You smile through the tears, holding tightly to his hands on your cheeks as you press yourself closer to him, “How are you feeling?”

“How am I feeling?” He laughs, “I’m fucking wrecked, baby. I’m,” He stops to laugh slightly as he sniffles, “This ended me.”

“You’re not going to stop the puns, are you?”

“Not anytime soon, no.”

With one last kiss, you leave Harry as you walk with the cast towards the stage, accepting Chris Evans’s hand as he helps you up the stairs before you all stand side to side, you between Chris Pratt and Sebastian.

“Your man’s crying tears of pride right now.” Chris leans to the side towards you, pointing at Harry as he stands clapping with everyone else, eyes set solely on you.

You giggle as you gave him a shrug, “Won the lottery with that one.”

“You sure as hell did.” Seb agrees.

“Do you all seriously have a crush on him?”

“Have you seen him?! You can’t blame us.”

You smirk, pointing at Seb with a tilt of your head, “Good point.”

Harry’s the last one to sit, a wide grin on his face as Robert begins to talk, making eye contact with you and giving you eager thumbs up and blowing you a kiss, mouthing a cheeky “I love you”.

You’re a giggling mess, discreetly flipping Seb off as he cooes, waving at Harry with the other as you mouth back, “I love you”.

Harry is full of pride, he’s sure that if it was possible, he literally would be smiling from ear to ear. And when it was your turn to talk? He couldn’t not stand.

“God, this has been a journey,” You chuckle as you talk into the microphone, “There’s nothing in life that will come close to how this lifetime experience felt. This was never about going to set, shooting and going home. It was about making a family out every single one of this cast. This has felt like home and no matter what happens, this will always be home. So many people I’d like to thank but that’s going to take all night so let me just say that, I love you all so much,” You turn to look at your castmates who watch you with love and smiles, “Thank you so much for the opportunity and thank you,” You smile at the audience as you reach your arm out, “For being amazing and,” Your eyes fall on Harry as he stands with a hand on his heart, looking at you, “For supporting us.”

//

title: My Prince
body:
